{
  "texts": [
    "In scenario 1, it has very little effect on the provider, but it has a good effect on good clients as well as on the core and edge routers.",
    "In the best route and multicast scenarios, it is very tough to avoid the CPA, which relies on the standard use of the NDN protocol.",
    "However, the given scheme only points out the effect of a CPA on NDN networks.",
    "The authors did not have any sort of solution to prevent the CPA.",
    "Nguyen et al. (2018) propose a security monitoring plane (SMP) that detects and mitigates CPA and interest flooding attacks in a testbed carrying real traffic by analyzing the NFD data-plane pipelines."
  ]
}